  <section class="page-detail">
   <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
     <div class="col-lg-9 col-lg-push-3 col-md-9 col-md-push-3 col-sm-9 col-sm-push-3">
      <article>
       <h2>
        Share the Season: Easy DIY Thanksgiving Decor
       </h2>
       <img alt="" class="attachment-banner wp-post-image" height="240" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Laura.1-680x240.png" width="680"/>
       <p>
        As soon as Halloween is over, Im ready to start thinking about Thanksgiving.
       </p>
       <p>
        I love Thanksgiving because theres none of the stress of buying presents and coming up with clever crafts and activities to amuse the kids (Elf on the Shelf, Im looking at YOU!)
       </p>
       <p>
        Thanksgiving is all about the food and the gorgeous harvest-themed decor.
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Laura.1.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11082" height="405" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Laura.1.png" width="520"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        Im a pretty good cook but admittedly challenged when it comes to decorating. Its frustrating to me because I appreciate tasteful decorations and a well-appointed home, but achieving it seems to elude me. Often I end up doing nothing because Im too afraid to fail.
       </p>
       <p>
        This year I decided to gather some easy, do-it-yourself ideas for making a beautiful Thanksgiving table. Surely with the proper instructions, I can achieve something lovely! Im determined to try. I put the word out to some of my talented friends, and here is what I came up with  5 gorgeous DIY Thanksgiving decorating ideas to inspire me (and hopefully you too!)Which one is your favorite??
       </p>
       <p>
        <b>
         5 Gorgeous DIY Thanksgiving Decorating Ideas
        </b>
       </p>
       <p>
        1. Check out this
        <b>
         <a href="http://www.momendeavors.com/2011/11/cornucopia-of-creativity-diy-thanksgiving-table-decor.html" target="_blank">
          Cornucopia of Creativity Thanksgiving Table
         </a>
         by Sara at Mom Endeavors
        </b>
        .I love how she gives you step-by-step instructions to make this happen. I think I can do this!
       </p>
       <p align="center" style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-the-Season.2.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11083" height="384" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-the-Season.2.png" width="519"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        2. I love the simplicity of
        <b>
         Whitneys
         <a href="http://www.mommieswithstyle.com/easy-thanksgiving-centerpiece" target="_blank">
          Thanksgiving Centerpiece
         </a>
         at Mommies With Style
        </b>
        .Just goes to show, it doesnt have to be fancy to be beautiful.
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/share.12.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11099" height="509" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/share.12.png" width="522"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        3.
        <b>
         Colleen of Classy Mommy shares
         <a href="http://classymommy.com/fall-decorating-inspiration/" target="_blank">
          5 Easy Ways to Inspire Your Fall Decorating
         </a>
        </b>
        . I love how she has fall decorations scattered about, lending a festive atmosphere to her entire home, inside and out.
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-2.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11084" height="352" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-2.png" width="519"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        4. I am obsessed with
        <b>
         Carries
         <a href="http://makinglemonadeblog.com/diy-thanksgiving-placecards/" target="_blank">
          DIY Thanksgiving Placecards
         </a>
        </b>
        . Now these might be a BIT of a stretch for me and my craft-challenged self, but I am pretty sure I could pull this one off. I love how she added a sentimental note on the back of each one, sharingwhy she was grateful for each person. The silver and gold pumpkins are so elegant. I will have to keep my eyes peeled for those when Im out and about!
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share3.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11085" height="387" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share3.png" width="516"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        5. Finally,
        <b>
         Kristins
         <a href="http://www.bonbonrosegirls.com/2011/11/fall-tablescape-for-the-leaf-of-it.html" target="_blank">
          Fall Tablescape: For The Leaf Of It
         </a>
         at BonBon Rose Girls
        </b>
        is so warm and inviting! She swears it is quick and easy to pull together, and I love how she plans to
        <a href="http://www.bonbonrosegirls.com/2010/11/one-glass-jar-two-easy-holiday-centerpieces.html" target="_blank">
         repurpose the glass jar
        </a>
        in the center.
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-4.png">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-11086" height="475" src="http://avaloncommunities.binaryminc.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Share-4.png" width="414"/>
        </a>
       </p>
       <p>
        Every single one of these ideas is conducive to apartment living and can be created on any budget. I cant wait to get started on mine!
       </p>
       <p>
       </p>
       <p>
        <i>
         Jo-Lynne Shane, of
        </i>
        <i>
        </i>
        <i>
         <a href="http://www.musingsofahousewife.com/" target="_blank">
          Musings of a Housewife
         </a>
         , is a writer, blogger, runner, community manager, wife and mom living in the suburbs of Philadelphia with her husband of almost 18 years, three lively children (ages 7, 10 and 13) and a terribly spoiled shih ztu named Savannah.
        </i>
        <i>
         She is a compensated participant in the AvalonBay Communities Share the Season influencer campaign.
        </i>
        <i>
        </i>
       </p>
       <ul class="meta">
        <li>
         October 31st, 2013
        </li>
        <li>

        </li>

       </ul>
      </article>
